time complexity: O(1)
space complexity: O(n) (where n is the size of the array)
energy implications: LOW

Explanation:

1. Initialize a map to store the weights of the elements in the array.
2. Calculate the total weight of the array by iterating over the map and summing up the values.
3. Generate a random number between 0 and the total weight using the rand() function.
4. Return the index of the element with the probability of picking it equal to the random number.

This solution has a time complexity of O(1) since the function only makes a single call to rand() and returns the index of the element. The space complexity is O(n) because the map requires O(n) space to store the weights. The energy implications are low since the function does not consume significant energy.

